  "beats": [
    {
      "num": "01 · the shape",
      "heading": "Autonomy multiplies blast radius",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "prose",
          "html": "<p class=\"body\">An agent is just software with a loop, tools, memory, and permission to keep going. That loop is powerful. It also means a bad assumption can repeat until it has touched files, calendars, customers, or money.</p>"
        },
        {
          "type": "terminal",
          "title": "agent · task loop",
          "caption": "The useful signal is usually already there.",
          "lines": [
            {
              "t": "$ agent run \"clean up duplicate invoices\"",
              "c": "pr"
            },
            {
              "t": "plan: search, merge, email customers",
              "c": ""
            },
            {
              "t": "blocked: email_customers requires human approval",
              "c": "err"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "graph",
          "center": "model loop",
          "nodes": [
            "prompt",
            "retrieval",
            "tools",
            "memory",
            "policy",
            "evals"
          ],
          "caption": "Hit the button and watch the hidden AI surface area light up.",
          "action": "stress the agent",
          "idle": "guardrails armed",
          "running": "probing weak edges...",
          "done": "6 AI failure paths exposed"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "num": "02 · the move",
      "heading": "Design the stop signs first",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "prose",
          "html": "<p class=\"body\">Before adding tools, write down what the agent may read, what it may change, how much it may spend, when it must ask, and where every action is logged.</p>"
        },
        {
          "type": "code",
          "file": "agent/permissions.json",
          "code": "{\n  \"read\": [\"tickets\", \"docs\"],\n  \"write\": [\"drafts\"],\n  \"requiresApproval\": [\"send_email\", \"refund\", \"delete_record\"]\n}",
          "caption": "A small permission file is more useful than a heroic prompt."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "num": "03 · the check",
      "heading": "Simulate failure before launch",
      "blocks": [
        {
          "type": "prose",
          "html": "<p class=\"body\">Run the agent against fake data with fake tools and real limits. The goal is not to prove it succeeds. The goal is to see how it behaves when the task is ambiguous, stale, impossible, or risky.</p>"
        },
        {
          "type": "lab",
          "title": "AI launch switchboard",
          "caption": "Flip the switches and watch the story turn into a tiny operating model.",
          "toggles": [
            {
